{"id":4559,"date":"2022-08-26T05:49:44","date_gmt":"2022-08-26T05:49:44","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/kjoumaa.com\/klima\/?post_type=dt_portfolio&#038;p=4559"},"modified":"2024-12-23T09:18:50","modified_gmt":"2024-12-23T09:18:50","slug":"fire-damper-for-comfort-ventilation","status":"publish","type":"dt_portfolio","link":"https:\/\/klimacontra.com\/products\/fire-damper-for-comfort-ventilation\/","title":{"rendered":"Fire Damper for Comfort Ventilation"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;4560&#8243; img_size=&#8221;450&#215;350&#8243;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><u>Description:<\/u><\/strong><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The fire dampers are intended to be installed in ventilation systems as cut-off baffles, separating the fire zone from the remaining part of the building. Hence why, the basic function of the KWP type fire dampers is the restrain the spreading of fire, temperature and smoke. In addition to that, with the usage of an appropriate actuator, it can have various usage in mixed ventilation systems (used not only in case of fire but also for periodic airing for example). These fire dampers are nonsymmetrical, intended for vertical (in walls) and horizontal installation (in ceilings).<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The fire damper is composed of two bodies made of galvanized steel, which are separated with insulating dividers made of 40 mm thick, fire-resistant material. Inside the fire damper there is a flap, which movement in closed position is limited with stop bar. The axles of the flap cooperate with slide bearings built in the insulating dividers. The closing of the flap is realized by system of flexible connectors.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><u>Tests and Certification:<\/u><\/strong><\/span><\/